The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 February is 37,571 (4,348.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 February, there were 1,917 new confirmed cases (221.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 January, there were 2,696 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (779 fewer cases).
